# Svelte 5 Compilation Constraints

## Runes (Svelte 4 Banned)
- State: `$state()` only. NO `let` for reactive data. NO stores (`writable`, `readable`, `derived`).
- Derivation: `$derived()` / `$derived.by()`. NO `$:` reactive statements.
- Effects: `$effect()`. NO `$:` side-effect blocks. Use `registerEffectRoot()` in ViewModels — never raw `$effect` in views.
- Props: `let { ... } = $props()`. NO `export let`. Bindable: `let { value = $bindable() } = $props()`.
- Events: `onclick={handler}`. NO `on:click`. NO `createEventDispatcher`. Use callback props.
- Slots deprecated: use `{@render children?.()}` and named snippet props.

## Views — Zero Logic (Structural Constraint)
- `+page.svelte` / `*_view.svelte` MUST contain zero logic.
- Permitted expressions: `{viewModel.property}` or `{viewModel.method()}` ONLY.
- FORBIDDEN: inline ternaries, `.find()`, `.filter()`, `.map()`, format calls, string templates, destructuring.
- FORBIDDEN: local `$state`, `$derived`, `$effect`, `onMount`, `<script>` imports from services/repos.
- Wrap in `<BaseViewModelContainer {viewModel}>`.

## ViewModels — Thin Bridges
- File: `{name}_view_model.svelte.ts`. Extend `BaseViewModel`. Export `getXxxViewModel` factory (uses `.create()`, never `new`).
- `$state` for UI-visible fields. Native getters over `$derived` for computed properties.
- NO heavy business logic, NO repository imports, NO API/firebase calls directly — delegate to services.
- `initialize()` calls `super.initialize()` LAST.
- Sub-view components: accept optional `viewModel` via `$props()` with default factory — never create in parent script.

## Banned Imports / Patterns
- NO `svelte/store` (`writable`, `readable`, `derived`, `get`)
- NO `createEventDispatcher`
- NO `$:` reactive statements
- NO `export let` for props
- NO `on:click|on:keydown|on:submit` event directives
- NO `<slot>` or `<slot name="...">`
